Rates are the number of reported offenses per 100,000 population
Crime rates are not available for agencies that report data for less than 12 months of a year.

Minnesota agencies 1993 and 2005-Present (with the exception of Minneapolis and St. Paul) - The data collection methodology for the offense of forcible rape used by the State Uniform Crime Reporting (UCR) Program does not comply with national UCR Program guidelines. Consequently, their figures for forcible rape and violent crime (of which forcible rape is part) are not included in this tool.
Sources: FBI, Uniform Crime Reports, prepared by the National Archive of Criminal Justice Data
